<div id="Food"></div>
<h2>Food</h2>
<p>There’s no denying that travelling isn’t quite the same without the great cuisines that you can taste along the way! New Zealand is not exception with its fab food! Here are the top five meals that we suggest you try:</p>
<p><strong>1. Hangi - </strong>If you’re a meat eater you’ll love this traditional Māori dish. It consists of slow-cooked meat and vegetables that is cooked in an underground oven. In traditional Māori culture, it is a special dish that is prepared on special occasions. </p>
<p><strong>2. Kiwi Burger-</strong> What’s not to like about a burger? It includes beetroot and a fried egg on top of the traditional burger patty- worth a try! </p>
<p><strong>3. Kina-</strong> Kiwis absolutely love their seafood. Kina is a sea urchin with a hard spiky outer shell and a deliciously fleshy inside. Don’t knock it until you’ve tried it! </p>
<p><strong>4. Pavlova-</strong> Controversial but apparently it is a Kiwi sweet dish (not australian!) Made of meringue, fruit and whipped cream- this dessert will be the way to your heart! </p>
<p><strong>5. Hokey Pokey ice cream-</strong> As a cool and sweet refresher, be sure to taste this Kiwi favourite! It’s caramelized honeycomb which is bound to tantalize your taste buds!</p>
</div>

